Package: libasmtest-dev
Architecture: any
Depends: ${misc:Depends}
Description: unit-testing framework for assembly language (development files)
 asm-test is a C-hosted unit-testing framework for hand-written assembly
 routines. It captures CPU register/flag state around a routine under test and
 asserts on the SysV/Win64 ABI, flags, memory and vector results, with an
 optional emulator and native-trace tiers layered on top.
 .
 This package ships the static library (libasmtest.a), the public headers under
 /usr/include/asmtest, and the pkg-config file needed to compile and link test
 programs against the core. The library is MIT-licensed and links nothing
 third-party; the GPL emulator engines are conveyed only by the separate
 language-binding packages, not by this one.
